uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.transition

Interface TransitionVisitor<X>

  • Type Parameters:
    X -
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractTransitionVisitor, DirectOperationTransitionVisitor, ServletTransitionVisitor, ShortcutServletTransitionVisitor, SwingTransitionVisitor

    public interface TransitionVisitor<X>
    Visitor to actually implement the transition logic. All changes to model state should take place within the TransitionVisitor. This returns a FormResult that encodes the new view/display state that should be implemented by a FormResultVisitor. The visitor pattern is used to ensure an explicit dependency between the types of Transition and the code that has to implement logic on them. Any additional Transition sub-types will either extend an existing type and use its implementation method or require a change to the visitor interface.
